\v 15 He had disarmed¦133409 the rulers¦133411 and authorities¦133414 and publicly¦133418 exposed¦133416 them, because he had won the victory over them \add ?≈on the post\add*.\f + \fr 2:15 \ft The meaning of the Greek ‘ἐν αὐτῷ’ literally ‘in it/him’ isn't clear here and leads to two common translations: a/ ‘on/in him’, or as we have chosen (interpreting the ‘it’ to be referring back to ‘σταυρῷ’ ‘execution post’ from the previous verse), ‘on the post’.\f*
\p
\v 16 \x + \xo 2:16: \xt Rom 14:1-6.\x*Don't let anyone¦133425 judge you all about what you eat or drink¦133434, or about \add observing\add* feasts¦133438 or holidays or days¦133442 of rest.
