\p
\v 10 \x + \xo 4:10: a \xt Acts 19:29; 27:2; Phm 24; \xo b \xt Acts 12:12,25; 13:13; 15:37-39.\x*My¦134133 fellow¦134132 prisoner, Aristarchus¦134130, sends his greetings¦134128 along with Barnabas' cousin¦134137, Mark¦134135. You've already received¦134141 instructions about that, so accept him if he arrives \add there\add*.
\v 11 Yeshua who's nicknamed Yustus¦134154 also sends his greetings. These guys are from strict Jewish backgrounds, but they're \add my\add* only fellow-workers for God's kingdom¦134165 who became an encouragement¦134171 to me.
\p
\v 12 \x + \xo 4:12: \xt Col 1:7; Phm 23.\x*Epaphras sends his greetings¦134172. He's \add another\add* one from your¦134176 place and a slave¦134178 of \nd messiah¦134179 Yeshua\nd* who always¦134181 prays for you that you will stand mature¦134192 and fully¦134194 confident in all of God's will.
\v 13 I can assure you that he has strong concerns for you all, as well as those in Laodicea¦134214 and in Hierapolis¦134218.
\v 14 \x + \xo 4:14: a \xt 2Tim 4:11; Phm 24; \xo b \xt 2Tim 4:10; Phm 24.\x*The dear doctor¦134223 Luke greets¦134219 you¦134220 all, as does Demas¦134227.
\p
\v 15 Give my greetings to the brothers¦134232 and sisters¦134232 in Laodicea¦134231, and to Nympha¦134234 and the assembly¦134242 \add that meets\add* in her house¦134238,
\v 16 and whenever¦134244 my letter gets read to you all, make sure that it's also read to those from the assembly¦134256 in Laodicea¦134255, and that you all \add also\add* read their letter.
\v 17 \x + \xo 4:17: \xt Phm 2.\x*Tell Archippus¦134268 to make sure to fulfil¦134278 the duties that \nd Yahweh¦134275\nd* gave him to do.
\p
\v 18 \sig I, Paul¦134284, am writing this \+add final\+add* greeting¦134280 in my¦134286 own handwriting. Remember me \+add here\+add* in chains.\sig*
\p \sig May \+add God's\+add* grace¦134290 be with all of you¦134292.\sig*
